HEADWORD: Main-gauche
<hw>Main`-gauche"</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧N`g⟦omac⟧sh")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., the left hand.]</ety> <fld>(Ancient Armor)</fld> <def>The
dagger held in the left hand, while the rapier is held in the right; --
used to parry thrusts of the adversary's rapier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

